Elevated plus Maze Test (EPM)
TheEPMisarodentassaytoidentifyanxiolyticpharma-
cologicalagents.Theplus-mazewasmadeofplywoodand
consistedoftwoenclosedarms(21.5×
×
 7.5 20cm)andtwo
open arms (21.5 ×7.5cm),whichextendedfromacentral
7.5 ×7.5cmplatform.Theplus-mazewaselevated38cm
abovetheoor.Weplacedtherodentinthecenter,andits
behaviorwasobservedandrecordedineacharm.Thetest
reliesonthenaturalaversionofrodentstoopenspaces,
thoughttoreecttheirinnatefearofheightsandpreda-
tion. A decrease in the time spent in the open arms and an 
increase in the time spent in the enclosed arms indicate an 
anxiety-likebehavior(Komadaetal.
).
